docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3222:Paul Smith's typewriter art (1921–2007) offers perhaps the most potent lesson in constraint-based creativity: born with severe spastic cerebral palsy, Smith created over 400 works using only **10 symbol keys** (@, #, $, %, ^, &, *, (, ), _), with each piece requiring advance planning of the entire composition. This mirrors the planning required for grid-based text art generation.
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3355:- Palettes: PALETTE_WATER, PALETTE_SPACE, PALETTE_CUTE, PALETTE_DRAGON, PALETTE_NIGHT, PALETTE_UI
