# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added deterministic PAL knowledge chunking (T-005@20260515T214233Z): `promptclaw.pal_knowledge.PALKnowledgeChunk` and `chunk_pal_source_files(...)` now turn configured PAL source files into stable, bounded, source-relative chunks with repeatable `pal-kb:` ids for unchanged input files, without writing runtime KB artifacts.

- Added PAL knowledge source discovery (T-004@20260515T214233Z): `PALConfig` now carries `knowledge_sources`, `promptclaw.pal_knowledge.discover_pal_source_files(...)` expands configured file/glob sources deterministically without network calls or runtime writes, and `pal-2026/promptclaw.json` declares the initial docs/ops/smoke/run-artifact inputs for later PAL KB chunking and indexing.

- Added PAL 2026 Agent Runtime v0: `promptclaw pal agent triage PROJECT_ROOT` lets PAL propose a diagnostic plan, executes only read-only allow-listed local tools, writes the plan/observations/final summary into the standard `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` handoff structure, and documents approval gates for any infrastructure mutation.

- Added PAL approval-gated actions: `promptclaw pal agent actions PROJECT_ROOT [--approve ACTION_ID]` gathers read-only diagnostic context, lets PAL propose fixed playbook actions, executes only explicitly approved allow-listed action ids, and records proposed, pending, executed, ignored, and approved actions in run artifacts.

- Added depth-2 wizard end-to-end test coverage (frac-0121): `tests/test_wizard.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `WizardEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `promptclaw/wizard.py` startup wizard surface through one realistic lifecycle: `init_project(...)` scaffolds a fresh temp project; `run_startup_wizard(...)` walks the base questionnaire (project pitch, task families, success outputs), defaults the agent roster to `["codex", "claude", "gemini"]`, queues per-agent strength questions, captures routing/verification/autonomy/ambiguity/boundaries answers, and triggers the `permission_boundaries` follow-up via the `"fully autonomous"` autonomy answer; the resulting project has every expected artifact (`prompts/00-project-vision.md`, `prompts/01-agent-roles.md`, `prompts/02-routing-rules.md`, `prompts/agents/{codex,claude,gemini}.md`, `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`, and `promptclaw.json`); the persisted vision contains the project pitch and approval-gate text; `load_config(...)` exposes the project description, `routing.verification_enabled=True`, `routing.ask_user_on_ambiguity=True`, the three default agents enabled with their `instruction_file` set to `prompts/agents/<slug>.md` and capabilities of `["coding", "implementation", "testing"]` / `["architecture", "specification", "verification"]` / `["docs", "synthesis", "writing"]`; the focused helpers agree with the lifecycle (`parse_agent_roster("")` returns the default roster, `looks_vague("anything")` is `True`, `mentions_any(...)` returns `True`/`False` symmetrically, `infer_capabilities(DEFAULT_AGENT_STRENGTHS["codex"], "codex")` returns `["coding", "implementation", "refactoring", "testing"]`, `lead_lane_text("coding, implementation")` returns `"code-heavy execution and implementation"`, `verification_fit_text("verification, analysis")` returns `"strong verifier candidate"`, and `sentence_or_list(...)` produces a single line for one item and a `- `-prefixed bulleted list for multiple items); the captured `output_func` blocks include the `"Startup Wizard"` banner and the `"Ready"` summary card; and a primitive diagnostic of the roster, applied config description and routing flags, per-agent capabilities and instruction files, the relative-path file list, and a focused-helper map round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_wizard_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `promptclaw/wizard.py` already produced the required lifecycle output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4685 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

